Step - 7: Predict and evaluate each model separately using the correct evaluation metric.¶

In [54]:
reg_models = ["LinearRegression()",
             "KNeighborsRegressor()",
             "DecisionTreeRegressor()",
             "RandomForestRegressor()",
             "SVR()"]

mean_results=[LR_mean,KN_mean,DT_mean,RF_mean,SV_mean]

result_df = pd.DataFrame({"Algorithm":reg_models,"MAE":mean_results})
result_df
Out[54]:
Algorithm MAE
0 LinearRegression() 4323.963298
1 KNeighborsRegressor() 3854.502497
2 DecisionTreeRegressor() 3057.492997
3 RandomForestRegressor() 2728.600419
4 SVR() 9114.819321

We can observe that out of all the models that we've trained, the Random Forest Regressor model is giving the lowest mean absolute error, which means predictions made by this model are the closest to the real values in comparison to the other models. So, we can say that by observing the evaluation metric of all models that the Random Forest Regressor is the best algorithm for the Medical Cost Prediction problem.¶
